      • ObjectField

        ObjectField(Field field,
            boolean unshared,
            boolean showType)
        Creates an ObjectField representing the given field with the specified unshared setting. For compatibility with the behavior of earlier serialization implementations, a "showType" parameter is necessary to govern whether or not a getType() call on this ObjectField (if non-primitive) will return Object.class (as opposed to a more specific reference type).
